{
  "texts": [
    "Another methodological consideration, and one that holds for all methods, is that while efforts to develop a DCT specification may result in one DCT specification, they may also result in multiple DCT specifications for each construct.",
    "The latter can happen when multiple researchers have different views on a specific construct, but also when an individual researcher develops their thinking about a construct.",
    "Intuitively, this might initially be perceived as not being helpful and resulting in more heterogeneity.",
    "However, the problem to address is not heterogeneity itself but its hidden nature.",
    "DCT specifications foster openness and these specifications are not in and of themselves right or wrong."
  ]
}